article.headline: Northern Illinois wins 6th straight, beats Toledo 38-15
article.description: Marcus Childers ran for two touchdowns and threw for another score to lead Northern Illinois to a 38-15 victory over Toledo on Wednesday night for its sixth straight win.
article.linkText: Northern Illinois wins 6th straight, beats Toledo 38-15

images.name: Northern Illinois returns blocked punt for TD
images.caption: Sutton Smith blocks Toledo punter Bailey Flint's running punt and returns it for a 27-yard touchdown.

video.headline: Northern Illinois returns blocked punt for TD
video.caption: Sutton Smith blocks Toledo punter Bailey Flint's running punt and returns it for a 27-yard touchdown.
video.title: Northern Illinois returns blocked punt for TD
video.description: Sutton Smith blocks Toledo punter Bailey Flint's running punt and returns it for a 27-yard touchdown.

article.story: DEKALB, Ill. -- Marcus Childers ran for two touchdowns and threw for another score to lead Northern Illinois to a 38-15 victory over Toledo on Wednesday night for its sixth straight win. Tre Harbison ran for 139 yards, and Marcus Jones added 101 yards rushing and a touchdown for Northern Illinois (7-3, 6-0 Mid-American Conference), which snapped a two-game skid against Toledo (5-5, 3-3). Eli Peters threw for 264 yards and a 23-yard touchdown pass to Jon'Vea Johnson for Toledo. Cody Thompson had eight catches for 110 yards. Childers threw a 33-yard touchdown pass to Corey Lersch in the first quarter and finished 13-of-19 passing for 131 yards. Sutton Smith returned a blocked punt 27 yards into the end zone late in the second quarter to give the Huskies a 17-9 halftime lead. In the third quarter, Childers bulled in for a touchdown from the 1 and broke loose with a 23-yard touchdown run to stretch the lead to 31-9.

videos.headline: Lersch breaks tackles on way to TD
videos.description: Northern Illinois' Marcus Childers dumps the ball to Corey Lersch who breaks a big tackle on the way to the first Huskies touchdown of the night.

videos.headline: Childers keeps the ball for a TD
videos.description: Northern Illinois quarterback Marcus Childers runs the ball 23 yards into the end zone to extend the Huskies' lead over Toledo.
